Nigeria has dropped one place down from 33 to 34 in the latest FIFA world latest rankings. According to the list published on Thursday, the Super Eagles also maintains its third position in the continent. The three-time African champions moved from its August tally of 1481 to 1482 in September. Senegal maintained their 20th spot, which is their best ever FIFA ranking and 1st position in the continent. Belgium remained top of the world ranking, while France moved up from 3rd to 2nd spot to unseat Copa America’s winners, Brazil. Ten top ranked nations: Belgium (1), France (2), Brazil (3), England (4), Portugal (5), Uruguay (6), Spain (7), Colombia (8), Croatia (9), Argentina (10th) Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.